  "description": [
    "IP Page Tw vt 183 chapters attending the 1948 convention of Delta Sigma Theta sorority in Kiel auditorium here recently heard four prominent panel speakers urge the election of congressmen in November who favor enactment of the Presidents civil rights program The speakersLester B Grang er executive secretary National Urban league Atty Sadie T M Alexander member of the Presi dents civil rights committee Philadelphia Dr Homer P Raine president Stepens college Co lumbia Mo and Dr Mary Mc Leod Bethune founder of Be thune Cookman college Daytona Beach Fla and president Na tional Council of Negro women were emphatic in their support of the civil rights program They went on record urging punitive nonpartisan political action in November by sending or return ing representatives to congress who favor the full program of civil rights In addition the panel asked that the civil rights committee re port be read and studied and that an educational program be launched to teach the American people the significance need and scope of human rights The five day meet which closed August 28 was highlighted by the presentation to Soror Alexan der of a beautiful plaque in rec I i lr The OHIO DAILY"
  ],
